criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age of 18-75 years;

          2. Normal renal function.

          3. Unilateral Renal calculus;

          4. Stent was placed at least 1 week before operation;

          5. Stones are fragmented successfully on single session of RIRS, and the diameter of any
             of fragments is less than 4mm，the imaging demonstrate the obvious presence of
             residual fragments.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Urinary tract anomalies, stricture or obstruction;

          2. Calculus in diverticulum;

          3. Severe hydronephrosis;

          4. Combined with acute urinary tract infection;

          5. Coagulation abnormalities;

          6. Couldn't tolerate EPVL;

          7. morbid obesity.
